---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navbar from '../../components/Navbar.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
import ParallaxBanner from '../../components/ParallaxBanner.astro';
import ContactForm from '../../components/ContactForm.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Best Restaurants in Cibolo & Schertz, TX | Cody Posey Real Estate"
  description="Discover the best restaurants in Cibolo and Schertz, Texas — from upscale American to authentic Thai and Tex-Mex favorites."
>
  <Navbar />
  <main style="padding-top: 80px;">

    <!-- Hero -->
    <div class="cs-hero">
      <div class="cs-hero__overlay"></div>
      <div class="cs-hero__content">
        <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
          <a href="/">Home</a> <span>/</span> <a href="/cibolo-schertz/">Cibolo / Schertz</a> <span>/</span> <span>Restaurants</span>
        </nav>
        <h1>Cibolo / Schertz <span style="color:#FF1616;">Restaurants</span></h1>
        <p>Local favorites and go-to spots in the area</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Intro -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <p class="cs-page-intro cs-page-intro--centered">The Cibolo/Schertz dining scene continues to grow alongside the communities themselves. From upscale casual to quick family-friendly spots, here are some of the local favorites worth checking out.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Expanded Dining Overview -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-title">
          <h2>The Cibolo / Schertz <span class="accent">Dining Scene</span></h2>
        </div>
        <div class="cs-content-block">
          <p>Cibolo and Schertz have undergone a remarkable transformation over the past decade. What were once considered quiet bedroom communities northeast of San Antonio have developed into thriving cities with their own identity, and the restaurant scene has evolved right alongside them. Today, residents have access to a diverse and growing selection of dining options without ever needing to drive into San Antonio.</p>

          <p>The anchor of the Cibolo dining scene is Main Street, where a cluster of independent restaurants has created a genuine downtown dining experience. Kindling Texas Kitchen leads the way, operating out of a beautifully restored 115-year-old home and serving regional heritage Texas cuisine cooked over open wood fire. It is the kind of restaurant that puts a small town on the map — thoughtful, ingredient-driven, and rooted in the traditions of Texas cooking. Right nearby, The Rooted Fork has become the go-to brunch destination, and Harmon's Barbecue provides no-frills smoked meats that deliver on quality.</p>

          <p>Schertz contributes its own strengths to the area's dining landscape. The Magnolia Pancake Haus, a San Antonio institution, has a location here that draws weekend crowds for its famous fluffy pancakes and Banana Foster specialty. Abel's Diner has been a Schertz staple since 1991, serving the kind of homestyle breakfasts and chicken fried steak that define Texas comfort food. Garcia's Mexican Restaurant rounds out the options with reliable, affordable Tex-Mex that has served the community for years.</p>

          <p>One of the most exciting developments in recent years has been the emergence of more diverse and elevated dining concepts. Mako's On The Creek stands out as a veteran- and family-owned restaurant that brings Caribbean and Trinidadian influences to its scratch-made menu. Situated along Cibolo Creek, it offers a dining experience unlike anything else in the immediate area and has quickly become a local favorite for both casual dinners and special occasions.</p>

          <p>For families, the Cibolo/Schertz area is exceptionally convenient. Nearly every restaurant in the area is family-friendly, with approachable menus, reasonable prices, and casual atmospheres that make dining out with kids easy and enjoyable. The breakfast and brunch scene is particularly strong, giving families plenty of weekend options that range from classic diner fare to more modern, Instagram-worthy plates.</p>

          <p>The proximity to San Antonio means residents also have easy access to the city's vast restaurant scene, but many locals find that they rarely need to make the drive. The combination of quality independent restaurants, reliable national chains along the FM 3009 and I-35 corridors, and a growing number of unique dining concepts means that Cibolo and Schertz can hold their own as a dining destination.</p>

          <p>As both cities continue to attract new residents and commercial development, the restaurant scene is expected to keep expanding. New retail and mixed-use developments are bringing additional restaurant space to the area, and the entrepreneurial spirit that produced places like Kindling and Mako's shows no signs of slowing down. For anyone considering a move to Cibolo or Schertz, the dining options are a genuine quality-of-life benefit that continues to improve year over year.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Restaurant List -->
    <section class="section" style="background: var(--light-gray);">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-title">
          <h2>Where to <span class="accent">Eat</span></h2>
        </div>

        <div class="cs-restaurant__grid">
          <div class="cs-restaurant">
            <div class="cs-restaurant__header">
              <h3>Kindling Texas Kitchen</h3>
              <div class="cs-restaurant__meta">
                <span class="cs-restaurant__cuisine">Texas Heritage</span>
                <span class="cs-restaurant__price">$$$</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p>Regional heritage Texas cuisine cooked over wood fire using local ingredients from farms, ranches, and the Gulf Coast. Housed in a restored 115-year-old home, Kindling brings a refined dining experience to downtown Cibolo.</p>
            <a href="https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Kindling+Texas+Kitchen+209+N+Main+St+Cibolo+TX+78108" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="cs-restaurant__address">209 N Main St, Cibolo, TX 78108</a>
          </div>

          <div class="cs-restaurant">
            <div class="cs-restaurant__header">
              <h3>Mako's On The Creek</h3>
              <div class="cs-restaurant__meta">
                <span class="cs-restaurant__cuisine">American / Caribbean</span>
                <span class="cs-restaurant__price">$$</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p>Family- and veteran-owned restaurant serving elevated American cuisine with Caribbean and Trinidadian influences. A scratch-made, seasonally inspired menu along Cibolo Creek makes this a standout local gem.</p>
            <a href="https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Mako%27s+On+The+Creek+169+Buffalo+Pl+Cibolo+TX+78108" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="cs-restaurant__address">169 Buffalo Pl, Cibolo, TX 78108</a>
          </div>

          <div class="cs-restaurant">
            <div class="cs-restaurant__header">
              <h3>Harmon's Barbecue</h3>
              <div class="cs-restaurant__meta">
                <span class="cs-restaurant__cuisine">BBQ</span>
                <span class="cs-restaurant__price">$$</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p>Authentic Texas barbecue serving brisket, sausage, chicken, pork, turkey, and classic sides. A no-frills spot on Main Street that lets the slow-smoked meat do the talking.</p>
            <a href="https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Harmon%27s+Barbecue+102+S+Main+St+Cibolo+TX+78108" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="cs-restaurant__address">102 S Main St, Cibolo, TX 78108</a>
          </div>

          <div class="cs-restaurant">
            <div class="cs-restaurant__header">
              <h3>The Rooted Fork</h3>
              <div class="cs-restaurant__meta">
                <span class="cs-restaurant__cuisine">Brunch / American</span>
                <span class="cs-restaurant__price">$$</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p>Modern breakfast and brunch spot serving dishes like biscuits and gravy, pancakes, eggs Benedict, and sandwiches with a twist on comfort-food traditions. A go-to for weekend mornings in Cibolo.</p>
            <a href="https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=The+Rooted+Fork+201+N+Main+St+Cibolo+TX+78108" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="cs-restaurant__address">201 N Main St, Cibolo, TX 78108</a>
          </div>

          <div class="cs-restaurant">
            <div class="cs-restaurant__header">
              <h3>The Magnolia Pancake Haus</h3>
              <div class="cs-restaurant__meta">
                <span class="cs-restaurant__cuisine">Breakfast / Brunch</span>
                <span class="cs-restaurant__price">$$</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p>Beloved breakfast and brunch restaurant famous for its fluffy pancakes — especially the Banana Foster — waffles, and classic American breakfast plates. A San Antonio-area institution with a Schertz location.</p>
            <a href="https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=The+Magnolia+Pancake+Haus+17730+I-35+N+Schertz+TX+78154" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="cs-restaurant__address">17730 I-35 N, Schertz, TX 78154</a>
          </div>

          <div class="cs-restaurant">
            <div class="cs-restaurant__header">
              <h3>Garcia's Mexican Restaurant</h3>
              <div class="cs-restaurant__meta">
                <span class="cs-restaurant__cuisine">Tex-Mex</span>
                <span class="cs-restaurant__price">$</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p>Traditional Tex-Mex and Mexican food including enchiladas, tacos, fajitas, and breakfast plates. A longtime local favorite that's been serving the Schertz community for years.</p>
            <a href="https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Garcia%27s+Mexican+Restaurant+3820+FM+3009+Schertz+TX+78154" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="cs-restaurant__address">3820 FM 3009, Schertz, TX 78154</a>
          </div>

          <div class="cs-restaurant">
            <div class="cs-restaurant__header">
              <h3>Abel's Diner</h3>
              <div class="cs-restaurant__meta">
                <span class="cs-restaurant__cuisine">American Diner</span>
                <span class="cs-restaurant__price">$</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p>Classic American diner established in 1991 serving homestyle breakfasts, chicken fried steak, burgers, and Tex-Mex favorites like migas. A Schertz staple for comfort food.</p>
            <a href="https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Abel%27s+Diner+17327+N+Interstate+35+Frontage+Rd+Schertz+TX+78154" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="cs-restaurant__address">17327 N I-35 Frontage Rd #200, Schertz, TX 78154</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <section class="section" style="background: #000; color: #fff; text-align: center;">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Thinking About <span class="accent">Moving Here</span>?</h2>
        <p style="color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); max-width: 600px; margin: 1rem auto 2rem;">Great food is just the start. Let me help you find the right home in the Cibolo/Schertz area so you can enjoy these spots as a local.</p>
        <div class="cs-cta__buttons">
          <a href="https://cposeyrealestate.idxbroker.com/idx/search/advanced" class="btn btn-primary">Search Homes</a>
          <a href="#contact" class="btn btn-outline">Ask About the Area</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>
  <!-- FAQ Section -->
  <section class="faq-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions About Dining in Cibolo and Schertz</h2>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>What are the best restaurants in Cibolo, TX?</summary>
          <p>Kindling Texas Kitchen is widely regarded as the top restaurant in Cibolo, offering heritage Texas cuisine cooked over wood fire in a restored historic home. Mako's On The Creek serves Caribbean-influenced American fare along Cibolo Creek, and Harmon's Barbecue delivers authentic Texas smoked meats. The Rooted Fork is the area's go-to spot for breakfast and brunch.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Are there family-friendly dining options in Cibolo and Schertz?</summary>
          <p>Yes, both Cibolo and Schertz are very family-friendly dining areas. The Magnolia Pancake Haus in Schertz is a beloved breakfast spot for families, Abel's Diner offers classic comfort food at affordable prices, and Garcia's Mexican Restaurant serves reliable Tex-Mex that kids and adults both enjoy. Most restaurants in the area have casual atmospheres and menus that accommodate children.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>What kind of food scene do Cibolo and Schertz have?</summary>
          <p>The Cibolo and Schertz food scene has grown significantly in recent years. You will find Texas heritage cuisine, Caribbean-influenced American cooking, authentic barbecue, brunch spots, classic Tex-Mex, and longtime American diners. The area has moved well beyond chain restaurants, with a growing number of independent, locally owned establishments that reflect the communities' evolving character.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <script type="application/ld+json">
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What are the best restaurants in Cibolo, TX?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Kindling Texas Kitchen is widely regarded as the top restaurant in Cibolo, offering heritage Texas cuisine cooked over wood fire in a restored historic home. Mako's On The Creek serves Caribbean-influenced American fare along Cibolo Creek, and Harmon's Barbecue delivers authentic Texas smoked meats. The Rooted Fork is the area's go-to spot for breakfast and brunch."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Are there family-friendly dining options in Cibolo and Schertz?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Yes, both Cibolo and Schertz are very family-friendly dining areas. The Magnolia Pancake Haus in Schertz is a beloved breakfast spot for families, Abel's Diner offers classic comfort food at affordable prices, and Garcia's Mexican Restaurant serves reliable Tex-Mex that kids and adults both enjoy. Most restaurants in the area have casual atmospheres and menus that accommodate children."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What kind of food scene do Cibolo and Schertz have?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "The Cibolo and Schertz food scene has grown significantly in recent years. You will find Texas heritage cuisine, Caribbean-influenced American cooking, authentic barbecue, brunch spots, classic Tex-Mex, and longtime American diners. The area has moved well beyond chain restaurants, with a growing number of independent, locally owned establishments that reflect the communities' evolving character."
        }
      }
    ]
  }
  </script>

  <ParallaxBanner image="/images/generated/cibolo-schertz-home.png" />

  <ContactForm context="I'd like to learn more about living in Cibolo/Schertz..." />
  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .cs-hero {
    position: relative;
    height: 280px;
    background: url('/images/generated/cibolo-schertz-home.png') center/cover no-repeat;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    text-align: center;
    color: #fff;
  }

  .cs-hero__overlay {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background: rgba(0,0,0,0.55);
  }

  .cs-hero__content {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
    padding: 0 1.5rem;
  }

  .cs-hero__content h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.5rem);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .cs-hero__content p {
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .breadcrumb {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5);
  }

  .breadcrumb a {
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5);
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }

  .breadcrumb a:hover {
    color: #FF1616;
  }

  .breadcrumb span {
    margin: 0 0.3rem;
  }

  .cs-page-intro {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: var(--gray);
    line-height: 1.8;
    max-width: 800px;
  }

  .cs-page-intro--centered {
    text-align: center;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--black);
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  /* Restaurant Grid */
  .cs-restaurant__grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .cs-restaurant {
    background: #fff;
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    box-shadow: 0 2px 12px rgba(0,0,0,0.06);
  }

  .cs-restaurant__header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }

  .cs-restaurant__header h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .cs-restaurant__meta {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .cs-restaurant__cuisine {
    display: inline-block;
    background: var(--light-gray);
    color: var(--gray);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    padding: 0.2rem 0.6rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.03em;
  }

  .cs-restaurant__price {
    display: inline-block;
    background: #FF1616;
    color: #fff;
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    padding: 0.2rem 0.5rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
  }

  .cs-restaurant p {
    color: var(--gray);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .cs-restaurant__address {
    display: block;
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    color: #FF1616;
    transition: opacity 0.2s;
  }

  .cs-restaurant__address:hover {
    opacity: 0.7;
  }

  /* CTA */
  .cs-cta__buttons {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .cs-content-block {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .cs-content-block p {
    color: var(--gray);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .faq-section { padding: 4rem 0; background: #f9f9f9; }
  .faq-section h2 { text-align: center; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  .faq-list { max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .faq-item { background: #fff; border: 1px solid #eee; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .faq-item summary { padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem; font-weight: 600; cursor: pointer; font-size: 1rem; list-style: none; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; }
  .faq-item summary::after { content: '+'; font-size: 1.3rem; color: #FF1616; font-weight: 700; }
  .faq-item[open] summary::after { content: '\2212'; }
  .faq-item p { padding: 0 1.5rem 1.25rem; color: #555; line-height: 1.8; font-size: 0.95rem; }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .cs-restaurant__grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .cs-restaurant__header {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: flex-start;
    }
  }
</style>
